Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
selectSecondaryPGNet(25.10)                        selectSecondaryPGNet(25.10)

Name
       selectSecondaryPGNet  -  Selects  Power/Ground  (P/G) net wire segments
       from specified instances

Syntax
       selectSecondaryPGNet

       [-help]

       -insts <inst>+

       {-net <net_name> | -pin <pin_name>}

       Selects Power/Ground (P/G) net wire segments from specified  instances.
       The  wire  segments  are selected from the instance P/G pins to stripes
       (swire targets). This provides an easy way to select and delete routing
       from specific instance P/G pins to stripes.

       Note: This command does not support dangling secondary P/G nets.

Parameters
       -help  Prints the usage of the command. For a detailed  description  of
              the command, use the man command:

              man selectSecondaryPGNet

       -insts <inst>+
              Specifies  the  list  of instances that have a secondary PG pin.
              Wildcards are supported in instance names.

              If one or more specified instances does  not  connect  with  the
              specified net, the tool displays a warning and ignores those in-
              stances.

       -net <net_name>
              Specifies the net name. This parameter cannot be used with -pin.

              Note: <net_name> does not take any wildcard values.

       -pin <pin_name>
              Specifies the pin name.

              This parameter cannot be used with -net.

Examples
              *

                The  following command selects the routing from the P/G pin in
                instance A of net VDD_1 to the power stripe:

                selectSecondaryPGNet -net VDD_1 -insts {A}

              *

                The following command selects the routing from the P/G pins in
                instances A and B in net VDD_1 to the power stripe:

                selectSecondaryPGNet -net VDD_1 -insts {A B}

              *

                The following command selects the routing from the P/G pins in
                instances A/B1 and A/B2 in net VDD_1 to the power stripe:

                selectSecondaryPGNet -net VDD_1 -insts {A/*}

              * The following command selects secondary  PG  net  through  the
                VDDO pin and checks all its ports:

                selectSecondaryPGNet -insts $instn -pin VDDO

                If  a  port of the the VDDO pin has an open, the tool prints a
                message as follows:

                **WARN: (IMPSPR-405): There is  no  route  for  secondary  pin
                "VDDO"   to  inst  "PD_CHIPLET2_PADS_PD_CHIPPADS_pads_out_bal-
                anced_ls_padring_chiplet2_u_DISP_LSYNC_C_UPF_LS" at  '3.085500
                1.902500'.

